# Commit/trace equivalence program (INVOKE success + observable check)
# Goal:
#   - Force the multi-cycle INVOKE path:
#       S_INV_ARG -> S_INV_WAIT -> S_INV_RES -> trace_commit_pre
#   - ALSO validate something observable:
#       store the INVOKE result to user RAM[0x80], then self-check it.
#
# Primitive fid=0x0001 has pops=2, pushes=1 in primtab.hex (base_cycles=12).
# The invoke stub + reference primitive for fid=0x0001 implement:
#   RES[0] = ARG[0] XOR ARG[1]
#
# Program:
#   push 0x1111, 0x2222
#   INVOKE 0x0001 => 0x3333
#   ST [0x80]     => user RAM write (observable)
#   LD [0x80]; push 0x3333; EQ; if false => TRAP
#   HALT

# 0: LIT16
6000
# 1: imm
1111
# 2: LIT16
6000
# 3: imm
2222
# 4: INVOKE fid=0x0001  (A=0x0, B=0x01)
B001
# 5: ST [0x80]  (OP_MEM=0x3, A=ST=0x1, B=0x80)
3180
# 6: LD [0x80]  (OP_MEM=0x3, A=LD=0x0, B=0x80)
3080
# 7: LIT16
6000
# 8: imm expected = 0x3333
3333
# 9: EQ (OP_ALU=0x1, A=EQ=0xA)
1A00
# 10: JNZ +1  (if equal, skip TRAP to HALT)
4201
# 11: TRAP aux=0x01 (should not be reached)
F101
# 12: HALT
F000
